Job Desc:
Location Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirate
Security Clearance Required? No Security Clearance Required
Position Description
This position is for a C17 Field Services Support Equipment Technician to coordinate the maintenance and calibration of Support Equipment in the United Arab Emirates. The position will initially be based near Dubai and will transition to Abu Dhabi when new facilities have been completed. The successful applicant will coordinate maintenance requirements and will plan, research, develop, analyze and retrofit repair solutions that comply with customer, regulatory, and Company requirements. They will also define the procedures, special tooling, kit requirements, work packages, and material requirements for accomplishment of inspections, modifications, improvement changes, and repairs of delivered products. They will plan and coordinate modifications, maintenance, and repair of enterprise products and assist engineering staff in planning and incorporating improvements. Responsible for assisting project development, planning, implementation, management, and technical support activities related to Support Equipment maintenance, modifications, calibration, proof load test and repairs per established customer, regulatory, and company requirements. Will also review and recommend projects and proposals for aircraft support equipment modification. Required to manage moderately complex or multiple projects, and develop, coordinate and forecast requirements. Will monitor project performance and risks and take necessary corrective action. A highly energetic, skilled professional is required to fill this position supporting the 24/7 operations of the United Arab Emirates C-17 fleet. The successful applicant will also be required to assist in the planning and the execution of the move from the current operating location to the new location in Abu Dhabi.
